parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption due to Defective Piston Rings
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potential engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Increased oil consumption
excessive oil burning
frequent oil changes
engine noise or knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden engine stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Engine stalling without warning
intermittent stalling
stalling at low or high RPMs
stalling while driving at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The continuous rebooting of the infotainment screen can cause many control functions of the vehicle to be inaccessible, leading to a loss of critical information and potentially affecting vehicle safety.
symptoms: The infotainment screen reboots continuously
never completes loading
and makes many control functions inaccessible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a visual seat belt reminder can lead to occupants not wearing their seatbelts, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: No visual seat belt reminder display
only an audible indicator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shutting off of the engine while the vehicle is in motion can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The engine shuts off unexpectedly
the vehicle fails to restart
the "start button" must be pressed until the vehicle starts
and the emergency flashers/hazard lights turn off and must be manually reengaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the rearview mirror glass can obstruct the driver's view, potentially causing accidents or near-misses, especially when changing lanes or reversing.
symptoms: The rearview mirror glass slowly tilts downward over time
pointing towards the backseat instead of the rear window
requiring frequent manual adjustments to maintain a clear view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate inspections and diagnoses by dealerships can lead to unresolved issues, potentially causing safety risks and continued frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships fail to replicate the issue
report "no issue found
" or do not thoroughly test the vehicle
leading to unresolved problems and repeated visits to the dealership.
